content: Texas Instruments' TivaWare Peripheral Driver Library is a set of drivers for accessing the peripherals found on the TM4C family of ARM Cortex-M4F based microcontrollers. Full API for configuring, enabling & using integrated peripherals are provided with support for multiple toolchains.
name: Driver Library

content: The Texas Instruments Graphics Library provides a set of graphics primitives and a widget set for creating graphical user interfaces on TM4C microcontroller-based boards that have a graphical display with support for multiple toolchains. Graphics library offers an easy to use API for rapid development with any LCD. The consistency across Graphics Library allows the same application code to be used across different LCD types.
name: Graphics Library

content: The Texas Instruments Sensor Library is a collection of functions and drivers for interacting with environmental sensors, such as accelerometers, gyroscopes, magnetometers, and so on with support for multiple toolchains. These sensors provide information about the environment in which the board is situated, allowing the application to make decisions based on its surroundings.
name: Sensor Library

content: The Texas Instruments USB Library is a set of data types and functions for creating USB device, host or On-The-Go (OTG) applications with support for multiple toolchains.
name: USB Library
